Printing Chart Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates the printing features available in Essential Chart for WPF which allows printing in color or black and white. It also allows printing a specified part of a chart using the cropping feature.</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\Printing Chart Demo.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph  FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16" TextAlignment="Center">
Fig: <Bold> Printing Chart Demo </Bold>
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Allows users to print a chart in color or black and white.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Supports printing a specified part of a chart.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Supports printing in both landscape and portrait modes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>Click the <Bold>Print</Bold> button to print the chart in color or black-and-white mode.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>Click the <Bold>Printing Mode</Bold> button to print the chart with an option for specifying the area that is to be printed.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>Select the <Bold>Printing Mode</Bold> combo box to print the chart either in <Bold>landscape</Bold> or <Bold>portrait</Bold> mode.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>


</List>


